            "aquascrubber-description": "A crude gravity filtration system that converts Salt Water into pure drinking Water.",
            "seabeetfarm-description":  "A small offshore agricultural platform for growing Seabeets, a sugar-rich aquatic vegetable from Zolarg Prime.",
            "aquamound-description":    "Higher class off-shore housing for an Insectoid family who can afford to live on the water, and away from the common nest.",
            "claypit-description":      "It might be messy, but an Insectoid feels great about himself after spending a day working in these Clay Pits.",
            "smolderingpit-description":"Throw a bunch of Wood and Sugar into a pit and light it on fire!  There is a lot of waste, but eventually, some Charcoal comes out.",
            "quantumsupplypile-description":"A mid-grade alien-tech infused upgrade to the Supply Pile, good for non-independent colonies that cannot build the Unholy Pit of Stuff.",
            "petroplant-description":   "Without regard for the environment, burn large amounts of Oil to produce electricity!",
            "microdistiller-description":"It's an offshore Salt Water Pump and Distiller combined into one compact unit!",
            "online-play-req-not":      "Online play requires a free Ape Apps Account.  Please sign in from the slide-out menu.  To create an account, visit https://accounts.ape-apps.com"   ,
            "gen-must-sign-in":         "Must be signed in to play!",
            "watervats2-description":   "Dug deeper and adorned with polished clay, your citizens will love gathering around and storing excess water in these lovely vats.",
            "houserunningrum-description":"A large public house in which high quality Food is served and Rum flows endlessly.  Hours of entertainment for citizens and tourists alike!",
            "laborcamp-description":    "A complex subterranean labor camp which employs and houses large amounts of insectoids, growing sugar and trees in an advanced underground process, while also conducting mining operations for Ore, Clay, and Gold.",
            "quantumfoodfortification-description":"Make the Quantum Leap in food processing with this alien-tech infused food fortification facility!  Creates an epic amount of food for a large population.",
            "megamound-description":    "A gigantic tourism structure specialised for holding a wide range of events, from sports to grand meetings.  Consumes Cloth, Food, and Water while producing Money, Civics and Research.  Also provides a small amount of shelters for workers.",
            "potterbugmound-description":"The worksite of a master Potterbug and his workers, where clay is baked into Pottery.",
            "megaconst-desc":           "Learn advanced building practices to start building large and tall structures that seem to defy gravity!",
            "insectdomin-desc":         "Learn to establish an absolute Insectoid Monarchy and exert control over your subjects across the galaxy.",
            "deluxecommand-description":"State of the art government command post for administering a far reaching Commonwealth or conducting business on a Federation level.",
            "unholytower-description":  "The ultimate storage unit for the Insectoid hoarder.  The only question you have to ask yourself, is will you ever be able to find something that you stuffed down into this unholy tower?",
            "glazedmound-description":  "When you need some more housing in the colony, try building this lovely glazed and painted Mound!",
            "smartpowerspire-description":"When simple Antaura based power isn't enough, throw some networking, microchips, and software into the mix and REALLY crank out the electricity!",
            "quantumslabofproc-description":"Nobody knew how to produce Bandwidth like the Ancients, so why try to improve on something that they already figured out?",
            "quantumwetcone-description":"Representing the ultimate in Wet Cone technology, for when you have a LOT of thirsty Insectoids to take care of.",
            "quantumcirfoundry-description":"Utilize ancient alien tech to crank out Microchips at a much faster rate.",
            "new-city-dest":            "Select new city build site",
            "unholygoldgrower-description":"Using the unholy power of Antaura and Crystalline, convert Ore and Antanium into Gold.",
            "crystalgenerationchamber-description":"This advanced mound facility takes massive amounts of Oil, Sugar, Ant Paste, and some Uranium, mixed with large amounts of Power, to create Crystalline.",
            "toweroftruth-description": "Spread 'truth' to the people, keeping them entertained (distracted) and generating some civics to go along with it.",
            "antaniumblastfurnace-description":"This giant furnace hardened with Obsidian will pump amount mass amounts of Antanium!",
            "etherreactor-description": "If you can get your hands on some Ether, you can generate large amounts of Power in a relatively small space.",
            "designatedswimarea-description":"Just a nice, safe, and relaxing area where Insectoids can swim without fear of being eaten by frogs!",
            "regobug-description":      "A hardy bug who loves to mine and collect Regolith!",
            "regolithincinerator-description":"Use Sugar to heat up Regolith to such a high degree that it breaks down into raw Ore.",
            "potofether-description":   "From childhood, young Insectoids hear tales of the magical Pot of Ether at the end of the rainbow.  Those are just fairy tales, but you can build your own Pot of Ether with a bit of Gold and some Ore and Regolith!",
            "etherbug-description":     "The only class of Insectoid who does not instantly die after ingesting Ether, so he is forces to live his life harvesting it.",
            "move-building-tip":        "Move this building to a different location.",
